div1.p: Office of the Sheriff of King County W.T.} ss.

I J H McGraw, Sheriff of King County W.T. do hereby certify that I receive the annexed Execution on the 13th day of November, 1885 and by virtue and in pursuance thereof, I on the 14th day of Novemeber 1885 duly levy, upon seized and I took into my custody in King County, W.T. as the property of the defendant named in said writ the following described personal property to wit:
2 Small Horses, 1-3 Spring Wagon and 1 Set Double Harness

That I advertised said property to be sold by me at the City Stables in the City of Seattle, King County W.T. on the 30th day of November 1885 by posting written notices of said sale in there of the most public places in said City.

That before the day fixed for said sale, to wit: on the 28th day of November, 1885, one Mrs Lena Hutchinson claimed to be the owner of said property, and having proved to my satisfaction the validity of her said claim, I by her order, left said property in the
custody of H. F. Phillips & Co in said County, subject to the order of her the said Lena Hutchinson
I hereby further certify that I am unable to find any property in my County on which to make the ammount of the said execution or any part thereof.
Dated at Seattle the 3rd day of December, 1885
J. H. McGraw Sheriff By D. R. McKinlay Dep.
Sheriff's Fees Levy $1.00 Copy Writ .80 Travel .20 Posting Notices 1.50 Copies 2.40 Travel .20 Swearing Keeper .25 Return of Writ 1.00 $7.35
